<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC5FFE9A1AA7D2991510D2E" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC5FFE9A1AA7D2991510D2E" blockId="12.[163,779,1650,1887]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A1AA7D29917A0CF9" box="[163,282,1651,1672]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Squids without a cornea covering the eyes; without suckers on the buccal membrane; without circularis muscles in the arm and tentacle suckers; without accessory nidamental glands; tentacles usually with carpal locking apparatus; gills with branchial canal; with duplications of the mitochondrial genes 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A1AA7C7090B60D4E" box="[163,214,1834,1855]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">atp6</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A1ED7C7191760D31" box="[228,278,1835,1856]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">atp8</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A02D7C7191360D31" box="[292,342,1835,1856]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">cox1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A06D7C7191F60D31" box="[356,406,1835,1856]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">cox2</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A0AA7C7191B50D31" box="[419,469,1835,1856]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">cox3</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A3197C7192260D31" box="[528,582,1835,1856]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">trnD</emphasis>
, although lost in some clades.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
